pull.title: 2011-12-16 "next"
pull.body:
This merges (including conflict resolution) various pulls ACK'd for 0.6:
- #677: API: GetMinFee modes
- #569: Coinbaser
- #669: Multisignature and OP_EVAL support
- #629: QR Code generation via libqrencode
- #582: Bitcoin-Qt signmessage GUI

events.message: Execute command specified by -coinbaser when creating a new block, which can output data to control where the generation goes
coinbaser: replace %d in command line with available funds
Support for TCP server coinbasers
Save coinbase, not just extraNonce
Replace nBits in coinbase scriptSig with arbitrary data set by setworkaux RPC call
Bugfix/safeguard: never create a coinbase scriptSig over 100 bytes long
Check for parse or overflow errors in setworkaux

Merge commit '96f9693' into coinbaser

Conflicts:
	src/main.cpp
	src/main.h
	src/rpc.cpp
Document -coinbaser option in --help
Port coinbaser code to Windows

Merge branch 'coinbaser'

Conflicts:
	src/bitcoinrpc.cpp
	src/main.cpp

Hand-merging:
	src/bitcoinrpc.cpp
	src/main.cpp
	src/main.h
Added QRCode generation functions via libqrencode
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin
Merge with addressbook changes
Collapse no-op ExtractAddress/ExtractAddressInner
Rework unit tests so test_bitcoin.cpp does not #include them all

Support 3 new multisignature IsStandard transactions

Initial support for (a and b), (a or b), and 2-of-3 escrow
transactions (where a, b, and c are keys).
Global fixture to send output to console instead of debug.log

OP_EVAL implementation

OP_EVAL is a new opcode that evaluates an item on the stack as a script.
It enables a new type of bitcoin address that needs an arbitrarily
complex script to redeem.
Put OP_EVAL string in coinbase of generated blocks
Disable addmultisigaddress if not testnet
Interpret OP_EVAL as OP_NOP until Feb 1, 2012

Use block times for 'hard' OP_EVAL switchover, and refactored EvalScript
so it takes a flag for how to interpret OP_EVAL.
Also increased IsStandard size of scriptSigs to 500 bytes, so
a 3-of-3 multisig transaction IsStandard.
Fix logic for IsChange() for send-to-self transactions.

Bugfix: fForRelay should be false when deciding required fee to include in blocks

During the rushed transition from 0.01 BTC to 0.0005 BTC fees, we took the
approach of dropping the relay and block-inclusion fee to 0.0005 BTC
immediately, and only delayed adjusting the sending fee for the next release.
Afterward, the relay fee was lowered to 0.0001 BTC to avoid having the same
problem in the future. However, the block inclusion code was left setting
fForRelay to true! This fixes that, so the lower 0.0001 BTC allowance is (as
intended) only permitted for real relaying.
GetMinFee takes a mode parameter (GMF_{BLOCK,RELAY,SEND}) instead of fForRelay
Merge branch 'minfee_modes' into next
Bitcoin-Qt signmessage GUI
Merge branch 'coinbaser' into next

Merge remote branch 'gavin/op_eval' into next

	src/main.cpp
Merge 'QR Code generation via libqrencode' into next

Merge branch 'signmessage_gui' into next
